55std::optional<SubresourceInfo> SubresourceInfo::decode(WTF::Persistence::Decoder& decoder)
56{
57 SubresourceInfo info;
58
59 std::optional<Key> key;
60 decoder >> key;
61 if (!key)
62 return std::nullopt;
63 info.m_key = WTFMove(*key);
64
65 std::optional<WallTime> lastSeen;
66 decoder >> lastSeen;
67 if (!lastSeen)
68 return std::nullopt;
69 info.m_lastSeen = WTFMove(*lastSeen);
70
71 std::optional<WallTime> firstSeen;
72 decoder >> firstSeen;
73 if (!firstSeen)
74 return std::nullopt;
75 info.m_firstSeen = WTFMove(*firstSeen);
76
77 std::optional<bool> isTransient;
78 decoder >> isTransient;
79 if (!isTransient)
80 return std::nullopt;
81 info.m_isTransient = WTFMove(*isTransient);
82
83 if (info.m_isTransient)
84 return { WTFMove(info) };
85
86 std::optional<bool> isSameSite;
87 decoder >> isSameSite;
88 if (!isSameSite)
89 return std::nullopt;
90 info.m_isSameSite = WTFMove(*isSameSite);
91
92 std::optional<URL> firstPartyForCookies;
93 decoder >> firstPartyForCookies;
94 if (!firstPartyForCookies)
95 return std::nullopt;
96 info.m_firstPartyForCookies = WTFMove(*firstPartyForCookies);
97
98 std::optional<WebCore::HTTPHeaderMap> requestHeaders;
99 decoder >> requestHeaders;
100 if (!requestHeaders)
101 return std::nullopt;
102 info.m_requestHeaders = WTFMove(*requestHeaders);
103
104 std::optional<WebCore::ResourceLoadPriority> priority;
105 decoder >> priority;
106 if (!priority)
107 return std::nullopt;
108 info.m_priority = WTFMove(*priority);
109
110 return { WTFMove(info) };
111}

129std::unique_ptr<SubresourcesEntry> SubresourcesEntry::decodeStorageRecord(const Storage::Record& storageEntry)
130{
131 auto entry = makeUnique<SubresourcesEntry>(storageEntry);
132
133 WTF::Persistence::Decoder decoder(storageEntry.header.data(), storageEntry.header.size());
134 std::optional<Vector<SubresourceInfo>> subresources;
135 decoder >> subresources;
136 if (!subresources)
137 return nullptr;
138 entry->m_subresources = WTFMove(*subresources);
139
140 if (!decoder.verifyChecksum()) {
141 LOG(NetworkCache, "(NetworkProcess) checksum verification failure\n");
142 return nullptr;
143 }
144
145 return entry;
146}

167static Vector<SubresourceInfo> makeSubresourceInfoVector(const Vector<std::unique_ptr<SubresourceLoad>>& subresourceLoads, Vector<SubresourceInfo>* previousSubresources)
168{
169 Vector<SubresourceInfo> result;
170 result.reserveInitialCapacity(subresourceLoads.size());
171
172 HashMap<Key, unsigned> previousMap;
173 if (previousSubresources) {
174 for (unsigned i = 0; i < previousSubresources->size(); ++i)
175 previousMap.add(previousSubresources->at(i).key(), i);
176 }
177
178 HashSet<Key> deduplicationSet;
179 for (auto& load : subresourceLoads) {
180 if (!deduplicationSet.add(load->key).isNewEntry)
181 continue;
182
183 SubresourceInfo* previousInfo = nullptr;
184 if (previousSubresources) {
185 auto it = previousMap.find(load->key);
186 if (it != previousMap.end())
187 previousInfo = &(*previousSubresources)[it->value];
188 }
189
190 result.uncheckedAppend({ load->key, load->request, previousInfo });
191
192 // FIXME: We should really consider all resources seen for the first time transient.
193 if (!previousSubresources)
194 result.last().setNonTransient();
195 }
196
197 return result;
198}
